---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="Globalization & Welfare State | Overview">
	<div class="hero">
		<h1 class="animate-in">Does Globalization Erode the Welfare State?</h1>
		<p class="subtitle animate-in" style="animation-delay: 0.1s">
			A panel data analysis of 32 OECD countries exploring the long-run relationship between 
			KOF Globalization indices and Social Security Transfers.
		</p>
		
		<div class="stats-row animate-in" style="animation-delay: 0.2s">
			<div class="stat-card card">
				<span class="label">Time Span</span>
				<span class="value">1980 – 2022</span>
			</div>
			<div class="stat-card card">
				<span class="label">Countries</span>
				<span class="value">32 OECD</span>
			</div>
			<div class="stat-card card">
				<span class="label">Observations</span>
				<span class="value">~1,200</span>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<section class="overview-grid container">
		<div class="card research-question">
			<h2>The Big Question</h2>
			<p>
				The "Efficiency Hypothesis" suggests that globalization forces states to retrench 
				welfare spending to remain competitive. Conversely, the "Compensation Hypothesis" 
				argues that states must expand welfare to protect citizens from international shocks.
			</p>
			<a href={`${base}/analysis`} class="cta-button">Explore Results →</a>
		</div>

		<div class="card key-finding">
			<h2>Key Finding</h2>
			<div class="finding-badge">Cointegrated Long-Run Equilibrium</div>
			<p>
				Our Kao Panel Cointegration tests confirm a robust, stable long-run relationship 
				between Social Globalization and Welfare spending, suggesting that the "retrenchment" 
				narrative may be overly simplistic.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="methodology-preview container">
		<div class="glass-box card">
			<h2>Methodological Rigor</h2>
			<div class="method-steps">
				<div class="step">
					<span class="step-num">01</span>
					<h3>Advanced Panel FE</h3>
					<p>Controlling for country-specific intercepts and macroeconomic shocks.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="step">
					<span class="step-num">02</span>
					<h3>Dynamic Specs</h3>
					<p>Using lagged variables and stepwise robustness to ensure stability.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="step">
					<span class="step-num">03</span>
					<h3>Validation Suite</h3>
					<p>Hausman, RESET, and Granger tests to defend against endogeneity.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.hero {
		padding: 6rem 4rem;
		text-align: center;
		background: radial-gradient(circle at center, rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.15) 0%, transparent 70%);
	}

	.hero h1 {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-weight: 800;
		max-width: 900px;
		margin-left: auto;
		margin-right: auto;
		background: linear-gradient(to bottom right, #fff 50%, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5));
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
	}

	.subtitle {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		max-width: 700px;
		margin: 0 auto 3rem;
	}

	.stats-row {
		display: flex;
		gap: 2rem;
		justify-content: center;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.stat-card {
		padding: 1.5rem 2.5rem;
		min-width: 200px;
	}

	.stat-card .label {
		display: block;
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		color: var(--accent-primary);
		font-weight: 600;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	.stat-card .value {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.overview-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 2rem;
		margin-top: -4rem;
	}

	.overview-grid h2 {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.cta-button {
		display: inline-block;
		margin-top: 2rem;
		padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
		background: var(--accent-primary);
		color: #fff;
		border-radius: 8px;
		font-weight: 600;
		transition: all 0.3s;
	}

	.cta-button:hover {
		background: var(--accent-secondary);
		transform: scale(1.05);
	}

	.finding-badge {
		background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.1);
		color: var(--success);
		padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
		border-radius: 6px;
		display: inline-block;
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		border: 1px solid var(--success);
	}

	.method-steps {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
		gap: 3rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}

	.step-num {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 2.5rem;
		font-weight: 900;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
		line-height: 1;
		margin-bottom: -1rem;
		display: block;
	}

	.animate-in {
		opacity: 0;
		transform: translateY(20px);
		animation: slide-up 0.8s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1) forwards;
	}

	@keyframes slide-up {
		to {
			opacity: 1;
			transform: translateY(0);
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 900px) {
		.overview-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			margin-top: 2rem;
		}
		.hero {
			padding: 4rem 1rem;
		}
		.hero h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
	}
</style>
